This paper deals with geometric networks and graph theory, which are closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of finding a minimum dilation spanning tree involves optimization and combinatorial algorithms, which are also relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents a hardness result, which is a common topic in graph theory (cs.GT).
